## Posts feed not showing results

## 1\. Check if you meet Voxel minimum requirements

Go to WP-admin > Elementor > System info, check your database version

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Make sure Voxel [minimum requirements](docs.getvoxel.io_articles_installing-voxel_.md) are met

- If you are using MySQL, the minimum version is MySQL8
- If you are using MariaDB, the minimum version is 10.3

If the minimum requirements are not met, you can contact your host provider and ask them to upgrade.

## 2\. Select the database type

Go to WP-admin > Voxel > Settings > Database and make sure you select the right database type (MySQL or MariaDB depending which one you are using)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## 3\. Recreate tables

Go to WP-admin > Structure > Post types > Edit your post type(s) > Filtering > Indexing Status > Press â€œRecreate table and index all postsâ€
